Toss chicken with dressing in sealable plastic bag. Add chicken with dressing to large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat; cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Stir in broth; bring to boil. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add beans; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through (170 degrees F). Remove chicken from skillet. Add rice and almonds. Remove from heat; cover. Let stand 5 minutes. Serve chicken over rice mixture.